{{Infobox language |name= Kayabí |nativename= |states=[[Brazil]] |region=northern [[Mato Grosso]] |ethnicity=1,620 [[Kayabi people|Kayabi]] (2006)<ref name=e18/> |speakers=1,000 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Tupian languages|Tupian]] |fam2=[[Tupi–Guarani languages|Tupi–Guaraní]] |fam3=Kawahib |iso3=kyz |glotto=kaya1329 |glottorefname=Kayabí }}
'''Kayabí''' (Caiabi) is a [[Tupian language]] spoken by the [[Kayabí]] people of [[Mato Grosso]], [[Brazil]]. Although the Kayabi call themselves ''Kagwahiva'', their language is not part of the [[Kagwahiva language]].
